HEADWORD: Falconer
<hw>Fal"con*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>fauconer</ets>, OF. <ets>falconier</ets>, <ets>fauconier</ets>, F.
<ets>fauconnier</ets>. See <er>Falcon</er>.]</ety> <def>A person who
breeds or trains hawks for taking birds or game; one who follows the
sport of fowling with hawks.</def> <rj><au>Johnson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

